The paper discusses the optimization of distributed deep learning training jobs, which involves parallel computing and optimization algorithms. This suggests that the paper is likely to belong to the Distributed, Parallel, and Cluster Computing (cs.DC) sub-category. Additionally, the paper focuses on deep learning architectures and their optimization, which suggests that it could also belong to the Machine Learning (cs.LG) and Artificial Intelligence (cs.AI) sub-categories. The paper also discusses non-linear programming and heuristic algorithms, which suggests that it could belong to the Neural and Evolutionary Computing (cs.NE) sub-category. Lastly, the paper discusses simulation and scheduling, which suggests that it could also belong to the Data Structures and Algorithms (cs.DS) sub-category.
